<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870917-0008 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Ohio Art Co.</HL><DD> 09/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> OAR LABOR </IN><TEXT>   Ohio Art Co. said it will stop distributing Britains Petite Ltd.'s line of typewriters, sewing machines, cash registers and other toys, effective Jan. 1. Last year, Petite toys represented about 9% of Ohio Art's $47.4 million in sales.    The Bryan, Ohio, maker of toys and the Etch A Sketch drawing device said Petite, a United Kingdom toy maker, plans to handle the distribution and marketing of its own line, beginning next year.    Separately, Ohio Art said union employees at its Bryan plant ratified a new 30-month contract, replacing a pact that expired Tuesday. Provisions of the new accord weren't disclosed.    In American Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Ohio Art closed at $51 a share, down 12.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>